<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,1629,2088]" pageId="7" pageNumber="129">
Culture characteristics:—Colonies growing on PDA medium, reaching 
<quantity box="[1034,1119,1629,1656]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="7" pageNumber="129" unit="mm" value="16.0">16 mm</quantity>
diam. in 6 weeks at 20 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1416,1444,1631,1654]" pageId="7" pageNumber="129">℃</emphasis>
, filamentous form, umbonate elevation, fimbriate margin, rough and glistening on the surface, green mycelia with white margin and orange center in the front view, reverse view dark green, white at the margin, center dark saffron yellow; producing yellow pigments on PDA, producing red pigments on MEA, no sporulation.
</paragraph>
