<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,1629,2088]" pageId="7" pageNumber="129">
Notes:—The distinctive characteristics of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. J. Y. Li, K. D. Hyde &amp; Q. Zhao" authorityYear="2022" box="[665,799,1917,1944]" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Chlorociboriaceae" genus="Chlorociboria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Helotiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="129" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="daliensis">
<emphasis box="[665,799,1917,1944]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="129">C. daliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are light bluish-green or faience blue disc and dark green to black receptacle when fresh, pale yellowish-green with jungle green patches or dark green disc and dark blue receptacle when dry, branched paraphyses, 76–94 × 5–7 μm asci with J+ apical ring in Melzer’s reagent and 9.8–12.7 × 2.6–3.8 μm, elongate to ellipsoidal ascospores. Tomentum hyphae are almost absent. Such traits are very similar to those of 
<taxonomicName box="[232,369,2061,2088]" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Chlorociboriaceae" genus="Chlorociboria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Helotiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="129" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="duriligna">
<emphasis box="[232,369,2061,2088]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="129">C. duriligna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[424,577,2062,2088]" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Chlorociboriaceae" genus="Chlorociboria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Helotiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="129" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="poutoensis">
<emphasis box="[424,577,2062,2088]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="129">C. poutoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1452,158,545]" pageId="8" pageNumber="130">
However, the disc of 
<taxonomicName box="[444,584,158,185]" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Chlorociboriaceae" genus="Chlorociboria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Helotiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="130" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="duriligna">
<emphasis box="[444,584,158,185]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="130">C. duriligna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is pale to dark blue-green when fresh, off-white to translucent blue-green when dry, tomentum hyphae are shorter and wider (10–20 × 3.5–5 μm 
<emphasis box="[947,977,195,220]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="130">vs.</emphasis>
23–30 × 2.3–2.6 μm) and paraphyses are unbranched (
<bibRefCitation author="Johnston, P. R. &amp; Park, D." box="[280,533,230,257]" pageId="8" pageNumber="130" pagination="679 - 719" refId="ref7662" refString="Johnston, P. R. &amp; Park, D. (2005) Chlorociboria (Fungi, Helotiales) in New Zealand. New Zealand Journal of Botany 43: 679 - 719. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 0028825 X. 2005.9512985" type="journal article" year="2005">Johnston &amp; Park 2005</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[551,836,230,256]" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Chlorociboriaceae" genus="Chlorociboria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Helotiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="130" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="poutoensis">
<emphasis box="[551,836,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="130">Chlorociboria poutoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is slightly greenish when fresh, bright yellow to orange when dry, and has a thin ectal excipulum (35–45 μm 
<emphasis box="[730,761,267,292]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="130">vs.</emphasis>
36–80 μm). Furthermore, the paraphyses are unbranched, the asci and ascospores of 
<taxonomicName box="[391,543,303,329]" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Chlorociboriaceae" genus="Chlorociboria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Helotiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="130" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="poutoensis">
<emphasis box="[391,543,303,329]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="130">C. poutoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are larger (95–120 × 8–9 μm and 13.5–15 × 3.5–4 μm, respectively) compared to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. J. Y. Li, K. D. Hyde &amp; Q. Zhao" authorityYear="2022" box="[136,269,338,365]" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Chlorociboriaceae" genus="Chlorociboria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Helotiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="130" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="daliensis">
<emphasis box="[136,269,338,365]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="130">C. daliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(77–94 × 5–7 μm and 9.8–12.7 × 2.6–3.8 μm) (
<bibRefCitation author="Johnston, P. R. &amp; Park, D." box="[804,1059,338,365]" pageId="8" pageNumber="130" pagination="679 - 719" refId="ref7662" refString="Johnston, P. R. &amp; Park, D. (2005) Chlorociboria (Fungi, Helotiales) in New Zealand. New Zealand Journal of Botany 43: 679 - 719. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 0028825 X. 2005.9512985" type="journal article" year="2005">Johnston &amp; Park 2005</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ren, F. &amp; Zhuang, W. Y." box="[1070,1304,338,365]" pageId="8" pageNumber="130" pagination="916 - 924" refId="ref8399" refString="Ren, F. &amp; Zhuang, W. Y. (2014) The genus Chlorociboria (Helotiales, Ascomycota) in China. Mycosystema 33: 916 - 924. https: // doi. org / 10.13346 / j. mycosystema. 130093" type="journal article" year="2014">Ren &amp; Zhuang 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1452,158,545]" pageId="8" pageNumber="130">
Phylogenetically, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. J. Y. Li, K. D. Hyde &amp; Q. Zhao" authorityYear="2022" box="[390,523,374,401]" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Chlorociboriaceae" genus="Chlorociboria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Helotiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="130" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="daliensis">
<emphasis box="[390,523,374,401]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="130">C. daliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
forms a sister group with 
<taxonomicName box="[820,973,375,401]" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Chlorociboriaceae" genus="Chlorociboria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Helotiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="130" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="poutoensis">
<emphasis box="[820,973,375,401]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="130">C. poutoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[989,1054,374,400]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1644,1666]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,662,1616]" captionTargetId="figure-220@4.[151,1436,662,1616]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Maximum likelihood tree based on a combined dataset of nLSU and ITS sequences, showing the phylogenetic position of Chlorociboria daliensis. The MP bootstrap values (ML-BP) equal to or higher than 50%, ML bootstrap proportions (ML-BP) equal to or higher than 70% and Bayesian posterior proportions (BI-PP) equal to or higher than 0.90 are shown above the branches on the phylogenetic tree. Newly generated sequences are shown in blue. Ex-types are shown in bold black." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6820906" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6820906/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="130">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) in the 
<emphasis box="[1143,1452,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="130">
<taxonomicName box="[1143,1302,374,400]" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Chlorociboriaceae" genus="Chlorociboria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Helotiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="130" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">Chlorociboria</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1310,1452,375,400]" pageId="8" pageNumber="130" sensu="stricto">sensu stricto</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
with 74% ML bootstrap support, 63% MP bootstrap support and 0.74 Bayesian probability. The pairwise homoplasy index (PHI) value resulted in 1.0, indicating no significant genetic recombination between them and confirming that they are different species (
<figureCitation box="[449,523,482,508]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[136,229,939,961]" captionTargetBox="[446,1148,210,896]" captionTargetId="figure-39@5.[431,1156,190,915]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. The results of the pairwise homoplasy index (PHI) test for closely related species of Chlorociboria daliensis using LogDet transformation. PHI test results (Φw) &lt;0.05 indicate significant recombination within the dataset." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6820908" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6820908/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="130">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Based on the macroscopic and microscopic morphological characteristics, we provided a taxonomic key of all valid species of 
<taxonomicName box="[681,840,518,544]" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Chlorociboriaceae" genus="Chlorociboria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Helotiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="130" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[681,840,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="130">Chlorociboria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
